Text Record Number: 31 gamma: 17 % likelihood of this document (based on its words) in this topic

Maybe you can check out the iPhone/iPad app ‘Paglano for piano’. It’s a simple shooting game for iPhone and iPad, by which you can train just one very small, but important aspect of reading music: finding the notes on your piano very quickly in all keys… This game is intended as a supplement to use at times and places when a piano is not available.
More info about the app: www.paglano.com
App Store: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/paglano/id1516800194

Text Record Number: 45 gamma: 17 % likelihood of this document (based on its words) in this topic

Maybe you can check out the iPhone/iPad app ‘Paglano for piano’. It’s a simple shooting game for iPhone and iPad, by which you can train just one very small, but important aspect of reading music: finding the notes on your piano very quickly in all keys… After playing it a lot you don’t have to count the notes anymore and you can focus more on all the other aspects of reading sheet music (This app is intended as a supplement to use at times and places when a piano is not available, but is certainly not a substitute for a real piano, of course…).
More info about the app: www.paglano.com
App Store: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/paglano/id1516800194
